title: Coffee Ceremony
description: The Ethiopian coffee ceremony is a revered cultural practice, embodying a sense of community and hospitality. Green coffee beans are meticulously roasted, ground, and brewed in a traditional 'jebena' pot. The ritual fosters social bonds as participants share in the aromatic experience, creating a cherished moment of connection over the nation's beloved beverage.

title: Kitfo
description: Kitfo, an Ethiopian culinary gem, features minced raw meat seasoned with spices and clarified butter. Served with injera, this dish showcases Ethiopia's rich culinary heritage and is a staple in communal dining, bringing people together over its unique flavors and textures.

title: Fasiledes
description: Enjera, a sourdough flatbread, is a fundamental element of Ethiopian cuisine, known for its slight tanginess. Often accompanying dishes, it serves as a versatile base. Shiro, a savory stew made from ground legumes and spices, complements enjera perfectly, creating a delicious and culturally significant combination in Ethiopian dining.

title: Holiday Food
description: Doro Wot, a quintessential dish in Ethiopian cuisine, is a spicy chicken stew celebrated for its rich flavors. Made with chicken, berbere spice, onions, garlic, and ginger, it simmers to perfection, creating a hearty and aromatic stew. Traditionally served with injera, Doro Wot holds cultural significance, often enjoyed during festive occasions and special gatherings in Ethiopia.

title: Abissinya Lion
description: The Abyssinian Lion found in Ethiopia has a large, dark mane, extending from the head, neck and chest to the belly.

title: Menilik Bushbucks
description: These little bushbucks are part of a sub-species found only in the Ethiopian highlands, and are very shy around humans.
